abstract: The 2016 contenders are exploiting loopholes and regulatory gray areas to transform the way presidential campaigns are organized and paid for.
snippet: The 2016 contenders are exploiting loopholes and regulatory gray areas to transform the way presidential campaigns are organized and paid for.
lead_paragraph: As the 2016 campaign unfolds, Hillary Rodham Clinton will benefit from one rapid-response team working out of a war room in her Brooklyn headquarters — and another one working out of a “super PAC” in Washington.

abstract: Tracking animals as they migrate across the globe is addictive: It’s hard not to see ourselves in their journeys.
snippet: Tracking animals as they migrate across the globe is addictive: It’s hard not to see ourselves in their journeys.
lead_paragraph: Displayed on a small plinth in a university museum in the German city Rostock is a famously gruesome exhibit: a stuffed white stork with its long neck pierced by an iron-tipped wooden spear from Central Africa. This unlucky bird survived the attack and flew back to Germany, only to be shot by a hunter in the spring of 1822. Newspaper reports revealed the spear’s distant origin, and the newly christened pfeilstorch, or arrow-stork, was celebrated for solving the puzzle of where German storks spent their winters.

headline_print_headline: Tracking animals as they migrate across the globe is addictive: It’s hard not to see ourselves in their journeys

abstract: Economic strife, immigration travails, drug and human trafficking, and myriad contemporary woes push their way up in the usual garden of filmic delights.
snippet: Economic strife, immigration travails, drug and human trafficking, and myriad contemporary woes push their way up in the usual garden of filmic delights.
lead_paragraph: Every spring, the Cannes International Film Festival arrives like a bright dream — a never-never land of cinema, star power and sun. But the festival does in fact take place somewhere in the physical realm, and France, besides hosting the world’s pre-eminent showcase of cinema, is a country with trauma in its recent past. The 68th edition of Cannes, running from Wednesday through May 24, arrives four months after the Charlie Hebdo massacre.

abstract: Who has it harder – the one deployed or the one left behind?
snippet: Who has it harder – the one deployed or the one left behind?
lead_paragraph: Who has it harder – the one deployed or the one left behind? After 13 years of war, I think it’s a reasonable assertion that the one in harm’s way generally holds the trump card. But there is another side. A friend of mine once said in a Christmas card that her son might be the soldier, but her daughter-in-law and grandchildren were the troopers.

headline_main: A Spouse Deployed, Still Fighting a Foolish Battle at Home

abstract: Acquisitions were once a symbol of the company, but the onetime Internet titan had in recent years been dogged by rumors of deals it should pursue.
snippet: Acquisitions were once a symbol of the company, but the onetime Internet titan had in recent years been dogged by rumors of deals it should pursue.
lead_paragraph: Soon after Tim Armstrong was named chief executive of AOL in 2009, he started reading the management book “You’re in Charge, Now What?”

lead_paragraph: ON THE RUN: Fugitive Life in an American City, by Alice Goffman. (Picador, $16.) This is a closely observed study of the criminal justice system’s impact on life in a poor black Philadelphia neighborhood. Goffman, a sociologist, spent six years in a community she calls 6th Street, documenting the routine police stops, raids and beatings that young men navigate. “The level of detail in this book and Goffman’s ability to understand her subjects’ motivations are astonishing,” Alex Kotlowitz wrote here.

abstract: Hillary Rodham Clinton will begin personally courting donors for a super PAC supporting her candidacy, the first time a Democratic presidential candidate has fully embraced the groups.
snippet: Hillary Rodham Clinton will begin personally courting donors for a super PAC supporting her candidacy, the first time a Democratic presidential candidate has fully embraced the groups.
lead_paragraph: Hillary Rodham Clinton will begin personally courting donors for a “super PAC” supporting her candidacy, the first time a Democratic presidential candidate has fully embraced these independent groups that can accept unlimited checks from big donors and are already playing a major role in the 2016 race.

abstract: Bentonville, Ark., a onetime backwater that is home to Walmart, is now crammed with new storefronts and tourist attractions, among them the Bentonville Film Festival.
snippet: Bentonville, Ark., a onetime backwater that is home to Walmart, is now crammed with new storefronts and tourist attractions, among them the Bentonville Film Festival.
lead_paragraph: BENTONVILLE, Ark. — It makes sense that the fate of this quintessential company town is being plotted in a conference room just a mile from Walmart headquarters. But what Trevor Drinkwater and his lieutenants are plotting is cultural, artistic and urban. In other words, something less stereotypically Walmart.

abstract: The push for reform is the strongest demonstration of a shift from a focus on national security at the expense of civil liberties to a new balance in the post-Edward J. Snowden era.
snippet: The push for reform is the strongest demonstration of a shift from a focus on national security at the expense of civil liberties to a new balance in the post-Edward J. Snowden era.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After more than a decade of wrenching national debate over the intrusiveness of government intelligence agencies, a bipartisan wave of support has gathered to sharply limit the federal government’s sweeps of phone and Internet records.
